#: ../../content/applications/sales/sales/invoicing/down_payment.rst:153
msgid ""
"If a down payment is used with a product that has a :guilabel:`Delivered "
"quantities` invoicing policy, and the cost of the product exceeds the 50% "
"down payment, a regular invoice is created. However, for products that cost "
"less than the 50% down payment, the down payments will not be able to be "
"deducted when it comes time to invoice the customer. This is because the "
"product(s) would have to be delivered *before* creating the final invoice "
"due to Odoo not allowing negative totals for invoices. If nothing has been "
"delivered, a :guilabel:`Credit Note` is created, which cancels the draft "
"invoice that was created after the down payment."
msgstr ""
"El sistema crea una factura normal si usas un anticipo con un producto que "
"tiene la polﺣ­tica de facturaciﺣﺏn :guilabel:`Cantidades entregadas` y el "
"costo del producto supera el anticipo del 50%. Sin embargo, cuando los "
"productos cuestan menos que el anticipo del 50%, no podrﺣ۰s deducir los "
"anticipos al momento de facturar al cliente. Esto pasa porque debes entregar "
"los productos *antes* de crear la factura final, ya que Odoo no permite que "
"haya totales negativos en las facturas. Si no has entregado nada, el sistema "
"crea una :guilabel:`nota de crﺣ۸dito` que cancela la factura en borrador "
"creada despuﺣ۸s del anticipo."

#: ../../content/applications/sales/sales/invoicing/down_payment.rst:161
msgid ""
